label.value: renal control of peripheral vascular resistance involved in regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: The renal process that modulates the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system, by impeding blood flow through the peripheral vasculature.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: The process that modulates the force with which blood travels through the systemic arterial circulatory system. The process is controlled by a balance of processes that increase pressure and decrease pressure.

label.value: renal vasodilation of the peripheral vascular system involved in regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: The renal process that modulates the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system, by vasodilation of the peripheral vascular system.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by renin-angiotensin

value.value: The process in which renin-angiotensin modulates the force with which blood passes through the circulatory system.

label.value: negative regulation of renal output by angiotensin

value.value: The process in which angiotensin directly decreases the rate of natriuresis and diuresis in the kidney.

label.value: positive regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: The process that increases the force with which blood travels through the systemic arterial circulatory system.

label.value: negative regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: The process that reduces the force with which blood travels through the systemic arterial circulatory system.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by local renal renin-angiotensin

value.value: The process in which angiotensinogen metabolites in the kidney modulate the force with which blood passes through the renal circulatory system. The process begins when renin cleaves angiotensinogen.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by neuronal epinephrine

value.value: The process in which the release of epinephrine from nerve endings modulates the force of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by circulating epinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of epinephrine into the bloodstream modulates the force of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by circulating epinephrine-norepinephrine

value.value: Any process that increases the force with which the cardiac muscles of the heart pump blood through the circulatory system as a result of the presence of epinephrine or norepinephrine in the bloodstream.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by neuronal epinephrine-norepinephrine

value.value: Any process that increases the force with which the cardiac muscles of the heart pump blood through the circulatory system as a result of the presence of epinephrine or norepinephrine released from the nerve endings.

label.value: renal water homeostasis

value.value: Renal process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of water in the body.

label.value: renal water retention

value.value: The process in which renal water excretion is decreased.

label.value: regulation of glomerular filtration

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular filtration. Glomerular filtration is the process in which blood is filtered by the glomerulus into the renal tubule.

label.value: glomerular filtration

value.value: The process in which plasma is filtered through the glomerular membrane which consists of capillary endothelial cells, the basement membrane, and epithelial cells. The glomerular filtrate is the same as plasma except it has no significant amount of protein.

label.value: pressure natriuresis

value.value: The process in which the volume of blood increases renal pressure and thereby results in both an increase in urine volume (diuresis) and an increase in the amount of sodium excreted in the urine (natriuresis).

label.value: renal sodium ion transport

value.value: The directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) by the renal system.

label.value: renal water transport

value.value: The directed movement of water (H2O) by the renal system.

label.value: tubuloglomerular feedback

value.value: The process in which blood volume is regulated due to a change in the rate of glomerular filtration. This is accomplished by a feedback mechanism that senses changes in the juxtaglomerular apparatus.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by chemical signal

value.value: Any process which increases the force of heart muscle contraction mediated by chemical signaling, hormonal, autocrine or paracrine.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by endothelin

value.value: The process in which endothelin modulates the force with which blood passes through the circulatory system. Endothelin is a hormone that is released by the endothelium, and it is a vasoconstrictor.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by circulatory epinephrine-norepinephrine

value.value: The process in which epinephrine-norepinephrine modulate the force with which blood passes through the circulatory system.

label.value: positive regulation of glomerular filtration

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular filtration. Glomerular filtration is the process whereby blood is filtered by the glomerulus into the renal tubule.

label.value: negative regulation of glomerular filtration

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular filtration. Glomerular filtration is the process whereby blood is filtered by the glomerulus into the renal tubule.

label.value: negative regulation of glomerular filtration by angiotensin

value.value: The process in which angiotensin directly decreases the rate of glomerular filtration in the kidney. Glomerular filtration is the process whereby blood is filtered by the glomerulus into the renal tubule.

label.value: negative regulation of the force of heart contraction by chemical signal

value.value: Any process which decreases the force of heart muscle contraction mediated by chemical signaling, hormonal, autocrine or paracrine.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by circulating norepinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of norepinephrine into the bloodstream modulates the force of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by neuronal norepinephrine

value.value: The process in which the release of norepinephrine from nerve endings modulates the force of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of heart rate by circulating epinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of epinephrine into the bloodstream increases the rate of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of heart rate by neuronal epinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of epinephrine from nerve endings increases the rate of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of heart rate by neuronal norepinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of norepinephrine released from nerve endings increases the rate of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of heart rate by circulating norepinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of norepinephrine into the bloodstream increases the rate of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: regulation of vasoconstriction by epinephrine

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of reductions in the diameter of blood vessels as a result of secretion of epinephrine into the bloodstream or released by nerve endings.

label.value: regulation of vasoconstriction by norepinephrine

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of reductions in the diameter of blood vessels as a result of secretion of norepinephrine into the bloodstream or released by nerve endings.

label.value: regulation of vasoconstriction by circulating norepinephrine

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of reductions in the diameter of blood vessels as a result of secretion of norepinephrine into the bloodstream.

label.value: regulation of vasoconstriction by neuronal norepinephrine

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of reductions in the diameter of blood vessels as a result of norepinephrine released by nerve endings.

label.value: regulation of vasoconstriction by neuronal epinephrine

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of reductions in the diameter of blood vessels as a result of epinephrine released by nerve endings.

label.value: regulation of vasoconstriction by circulating epinephrine

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of reductions in the diameter of blood vessels as a result of secretion of epinephrine into the bloodstream.

label.value: epinephrine-mediated vasodilation

value.value: A vasodilation process resulting from secretion of epinephrine into the bloodstream or released by nerve endings.

label.value: norepinephrine-mediated vasodilation

value.value: A vasodilation process resulting from secretion of norepinephrine into the bloodstream or released by nerve endings.

label.value: detection of nodal flow

value.value: The series of events by which an endogenous stimulus is received by a cilium on a cell and converted to a molecular signal contributing to left/right asymmetry.

label.value: heart field specification

value.value: The process that results in the delineation of a specific region of the lateral mesoderm into the area in which the heart will develop.

label.value: heart induction

value.value: The close range interaction between mesoderm and endoderm or ectoderm that causes cells to change their fates and specify the development of the heart.

label.value: mesodermal-endodermal cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from mesodermal cells to endodermal cells.

label.value: mesodermal-endodermal cell signaling involved in heart induction

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from mesodermal cells to endodermal cells that contributes to heart induction.

label.value: endodermal-mesodermal cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from endodermal cells to mesodermal cells.

label.value: endodermal-mesodermal cell signaling involved in heart induction

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from endodermal cells to mesodermal cells that contributes to heart induction.

label.value: primary heart field specification

value.value: The process that results in the delineation of a specific region of the lateral mesoderm into the area which will form the primary beating heart tube. In mammals the primary heart field gives rise to the left ventricle.

label.value: secondary heart field specification

value.value: The process that results in the delineation of a specific region of the lateral mesoderm into the area which will form the majority of the mesodermal component of the right ventricle, arterial pole (outflow tract) and venous pole (inflow tract).
